s behave a little different when girls are watching, and i also found boys were quite good at limiting the bitchyness girls are renowned for. So both kept one another in line, and made for a more positive and dynamic environment. &#10;I also think there's a few extra life lessons and skills children can learn at co ed schools. Dating, relationships, interacting with the opposite sex, i think children at co ed schools tend to have a far better grasp of these skills then students who've only attended same sex schools. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="821" language="en" documentId="2180" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Rika-san" date="2012-May-14, 1:27 pm" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://whrl.pl/RdbtZz" topic="single-sex-education" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="2180" notes="" title="Girls to Co-Ed or all girls high school"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="24"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="25" end="533"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="534" end="821"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47"/></xmi:XMI>